Wrapper function for ctk's bed2rgb

ctk_tag2profile.Rd

Wrapper function for ctk's bed2rgb

ctk_tag2profile(
  filesToRun,
  outFile = paste0(file_path_sans_ext(filesToRun), ".out"),
  outFile2 = NULL,
  sb = "tag2profile.pl",
  perl = "perl",
  PATHTOPERLLIB = NULL,
  bigFile = FALSE,
  weight = FALSE,
  weightAvg = FALSE,
  ss = TRUE,
  exact = TRUE,
  nz = FALSE,
  ext5 = NULL,
  ext3 = NULL,
  chromLen = NULL,
  region = NULL,
  minBlockSize = 2e+06,
  windowSize = 100,
  stepSize = 20,
  outputFormat = "bedgraph",
  normalization = "none",
  stderr = paste0(getwd(), "stripBarcode_stderr"),
  stdout = paste0(getwd(), "stripBarcode_stdout"),
  useClipRConda = ifelse(is.null(getOption("CLIPflexR.condaEnv")), FALSE, TRUE),
  additionalArgumements = NULL,
  verbose = FALSE
)

Arguments

filesToRun

File to process.
outFile

Output file
outFile2

Output 2 file
sb

Path to tag2collapse.pl from FastX toolkit
perl

Path to PERL
PATHTOPERLLIB

Path to PERL5LIB.
bigFile

TRUE when working with a big file
weight

weight counts according to the score of each tag
weightAvg

weight average the score of each tag
ss

separate strand
exact

exact count at each nucleotide
nz

don't print zeroes (works for sgr and bed)
ext5

extension of tags at the 5' end
ext3

extension of tags at the 3' end
chromLen

chrom length file
region

a bed file with regions to count tag numbers. If not specified, count in moving windows
minBlockSize

minimum number of lines to read in each block for a big file
windowSize

Window size
stepSize

Step size
outputFormat

output format ([bed] or bedgraph or sgr)
normalization

normalization ([none] or rpkm or multiply=1.3)
stderr

Path to stdout file.
stdout

Path to stdout file.
useClipRConda

Boolean on whether to use conda environment install by CondaSysReqs
additionalArgumements

Additional arguments to be passed to system call.
verbose

Print more message to screen.

Value

Path to unzipped file
